        "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
        "old_string": "  \"text\": \"The k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object interface is defined in k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/interfaces.go (line 336) and requires types to implement GetObjectKind() and DeepCopyObject() methods. The interface is implemented in the k8s.io/api/core/v1 package by embedding metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta, which are defined in k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go. TypeMeta (line 42) contains Kind and APIVersion fields, while ObjectMeta (line 111) contains metadata fields like Name, Namespace, UID, etc. The k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go file defines 39 core API types that implement runtime.Object, including Pod, Service, Node, Namespace, Secret, ConfigMap, PersistentVolume, Event, and others. These types are registered into the runtime scheme via k8s.io/api/core/v1/register.go in the addKnownTypes() function (line 45), which calls scheme.AddKnownTypes() to register each type with the SchemeGroupVersion. The kubernetes/kubernetes repository mirrors this structure in its staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/ directory, which contains identical copies of types.go and register.go. Additionally, kubernetes/kubernetes/pkg/apis/core/v1/register.go references the external k8s.io/api types and registers conversion and defaulting functions. The apimachinery module defines the fundamental interfaces and metadata structures that all Kubernetes API types depend on, establishing a clean separation between the core runtime interfaces and the concrete API type implementations.\"",
        "new_string": "  \"text\": \"The k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object interface is defined in k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/interfaces.go (line 336) and requires types to implement GetObjectKind() and DeepCopyObject() methods. The interface is implemented in the k8s.io/api/core/v1 package by embedding metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta, which are defined in k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go. TypeMeta (line 42) contains Kind and APIVersion fields, while ObjectMeta (line 111) contains metadata fields like Name, Namespace, UID, etc. The k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go file defines 44 core API types that implement runtime.Object, including Pod, Service, Node, Namespace, Secret, ConfigMap, PersistentVolume, Event, and others. These types are registered into the runtime scheme via k8s.io/api/core/v1/register.go in the addKnownTypes() function (line 45), which calls scheme.AddKnownTypes() to register each type with the SchemeGroupVersion. The kubernetes/kubernetes repository mirrors this structure in its staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/ directory, which contains identical copies of types.go and register.go. Additionally, kubernetes/kubernetes/pkg/apis/core/v1/register.go references the external k8s.io/api types and registers conversion and defaulting functions. The apimachinery module defines the fundamental interfaces and metadata structures that all Kubernetes API types depend on, establishing a clean separation between the core runtime interfaces and the concrete API type implementations.\"",
